  childSummary:"A robot is a machine that can SENSE things around it (using cameras and sensors — like our eyes and touch), THINK about what to do (using a computer brain running smart programs), and ACT on the world (using motors to move arms, wheels, or grippers — like our muscles). Factory robots are like super-precise arms that can weld, paint, and assemble things all day without getting tired — with accuracy better than 0.02 millimeters! Surgical robots help doctors operate through tiny 1-centimeter cuts instead of big openings, and they filter out the doctor's hand trembling for super-steady precision. Warehouse robots zip around Amazon and Flipkart warehouses carrying your packages. India has only 4 robots per 10,000 factory workers (South Korea has 1,000!) — but that number is growing fast. The coolest new robots are HUMANOIDS like Boston Dynamics' Atlas that can do backflips, and Tesla's Optimus that might one day help around the house!",
  applications:["Industrial manufacturing (welding, painting, assembly)","Warehouse logistics (picking, packing, sorting, transportation)","Surgical assistance (da Vinci — minimally invasive surgery)","Agricultural automation (drone spraying, weeding, harvesting)","Defense and security (surveillance, bomb disposal, patrol)","Healthcare (rehabilitation, elderly care, hospital logistics)","Education and companionship (Miko, Pepper)","Construction (3D printing, demolition, inspection)","Space exploration (Mars rovers, satellite servicing)","Underwater exploration (pipeline inspection, ocean research)"],
